		+section('A message from Selina Esteves')
			+p
				| A year ago, the world challenged us to change how we think and operate. March marks the one-year anniversary of the Faculty’s adjustment to the pandemic. We are happy to share stories about our successful adaptation to online teaching, how exciting new technologies at the Faculty support our students and patients, and how our Class of 2T0 transitioned to life after graduation.
			+p 
				| March also marks Women’s History Month. We feature a pioneering alumna, Margaret Hatton 5T2 PhD and an opinion piece by alumna and soon-to-be CDA president-elect Lynn Tomkins 8T1. It has been a year of challenges. Undoubtedly, more will come. But with spring nearly here and the continued support of our alumni, donors, faculty, staff and friends, we celebrate the excellence and resilience of U of T Dentistry.
			| Sincerely,
			br
			| Selina Esteves
			br
			| Director, Advancement and Alumni Relations
